<headline>Special Weather Statement issued January 25 at 11:26AM EST  by NWS Detroit</headline>
<description>...A WINTER STORM WARNING REMAINS IN EFFECT...
Bands of higher intensity snowfall will begin to lift into the
area over the next several hours. Snowfall rates may exceed a half
inch per hour at times with these bands, resulting in additional
snow accumulations of 1 to 2 inches through 2 PM with localized
higher amounts possible. Motorists should be prepared for
variable road conditions as temperatures hold between 32 and 34
degrees, with snow covered and slick conditions worsening on
untreated roadways. Visibility may be reduced to a half mile or
less at times. Slow down and use caution if traveling this
afternoon.</description>
